title: Structure of cross section of the (gamma,n) reaction on nuclei Si-28, S-32, and Ca-40.

x4freetext: Structure of cross section of the (gamma,n) reaction
on nuclei Si-28, S-32, and Ca-40.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Soviet Journal of Nuclear Physics, Vol.7, p.698 (1968)

x4freetext: - Eng.trans.of YF,7,1168,1968
The multichannel method  of the reaction yield
measurement was  used  in  which  the  bremmstrahlung
end-point  energy  has  been changed automatically in
each cycle of electron acceleration in betatron  with
50 Hz frequency.
The  natural  silicon  (abundance  -  92.23%),
sulphur (95.02%), and calcium  (96.94%) samples  were
used  as  the  targets,  all  three have the shape of
cylinder with the diameter of  40  mm  and  thickness
about 10 g/cm-2.
The  Penfold - Leiss  unfolding   method   with
the different  bins  was  used  for  obtaining  cross
section data from experimental yield curve.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Mean root-square errors are given.
The data have been digitized in the CDFE.
By  means  of  direct registration  the  curves of the
photoneutron yields  were measured from the threshold
of the reaction (gamma,n) up to 30 MeV for Si-28, S-32
and Ca-40. The (gamma,n) reaction cross sections
obtained are compared with the calculations performed
within the framework  of  the particle-hole approach.
It is shown that for the Si-28 and S-32 the
configurational splitting of  the giant resonance is
main effect that determines the  gross  structure  of
(gamma,n)  reaction cross section.
Absolute cross section  data  were  obtained using the
comparison procedure for thin targets (2 g/cm-2)
of element  studied  and  the  data for copper target
from the measurement of H.H.Thies et. al.

reaction cross section was measured but the threshold
of (gamma,np) reaction is 24.6 MeV and that of
(gamma,2n) - 30.5 MeV.
